  <history>Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from HDX. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase. The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Admin0 p-codes changed to 2-letter ISO code. 2. Donut holes for lakes were filled. 3. As instructed by UNOCHA, the Admin2 features "Emurua Dikirr", "Kilgoris" and "Narok West" now have attribution for Admin1 "Narok". "Emurua Dikirr" now has Admin2 p-code "KE033178", "Kilgoris" has "KE033177" and "Narok West" has "KE033182". </history>
